      Parameters:

    • versionCompare

      public static int versionCompare(String v1, String v2)
      Handles comparison between version numbers (the right way(TM)). Examples of version strings: 1.6.7, 1.2_b10
      Parameters:
      v1 - the first version to compare.
      v2 - the second version to compare.
      Returns:
      a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as the first argument is less than, equal to, or greater than the second.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the version number are not proper (i.e. the do not comply with the following regular expression [0-9]+(.[0-9]+)*(_[a-zA-Z0-9]+)?
